                <img src="~/Content/screenshot-hud-ajax.gif" class="img-responsive target" data-target="3" style="position: absolute;" />
            </div>
        </div>
        <div style="background-color: #F1F1F2;">
            <div class="container is-container-items" style="margin-bottom: 50px; padding-top: 50px; padding-bottom: 75px;">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-4 media">
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-save pull-left"></span>
                        <div class="media-body">
                            <h4 class="media-heading">Install via NuGet</h4>
                            <p>Glimpse is installed with one simple NuGet command (<samp>Install-Package Glimpse</samp>) or with Visual Studio's manager package dialog.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-4 media">
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-cog pull-left"></span>
                        <div class="media-body">
                            <h4 class="media-heading">Extensible & Configurable</h4>
                            <p>Extend Glimpse via simple <abbr title="Application Programming Interface">API</abbr>s and our 3<sup>rd</sup> party NuGet package ecosystem. Configure it on a whim with the <code>~/Glimpse.axd</code> configuration builder and <code>web.config</code>.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-4 media">
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-cloud pull-left"></span>
                        <div class="media-body">
                            <h4 class="media-heading">Web Native</h4>
                            <p>Glimpse is built with web technologies that you love: <abbr title="Hypertext Markup Language">HTML</abbr>, <abbr title="Cascading Style Sheets">CSS</abbr> & <abbr title="JavaScript">JS</abbr>. It requires no proprietary browser plugin and works everywhere you do.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-4 media">
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-lock pull-left"></span>
                        <div class="media-body">
                            <h4 class="media-heading">Hardened Security</h4>
                            <p>Hardened by default, only you get to choose who can see wht Glimpse data and when. Check out <code>GlimpseSecurityPolicy.cs</code>, already in you project, for more information and samples.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-4 media">
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flash pull-left"></span>
                        <div class="media-body">
                            <h4 class="media-heading">Lightweight & Fast</h4>
                            <p>Glimpse's unique architecture makes it faster and less resource intensive than traditional profilers so you never have to sacrifice performance.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-4 media">
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-eye-open pull-left"></span>
                        <div class="media-body">
                            <h4 class="media-heading">Unique Perspective</h4>
                            <p>While F12 tools like <a href="http://getfirebug.com/">Firebug</a> and proxy debuggers like <a href="http://www.telerik.com/fiddler">Fiddler</a> are extremely useful, only Glimpse provides diagnostics from the perspective of your server.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>


